"The work began in September 2022 according to a programmed activity that was ending in these days with contractors among the most prestigious companies in the world," said Bernabei, who mentioned among others the name of Siemens, "the contractors can turn to other specialists, because here the works can only be done by specialists".
<h2> The reaction of the unions
Cgil> and Uil declared for the day of April 11 an eight-hour strike in all sectors and convened a demonstration in Bologna, in Piazza XX Settembre, "which holds together the dismay and anger, because after a day we do not know the companies involved, what happened, that contracts had the workers in various ways involved in an Enel yard", said Michele Bulgarelli, secretary of the Cgil of the Emilian capital. "This is Italy, this is the world of work... What did a 73-year-old pensioner do for us in a construction site?", the trade unionist continued, "bass: we need to keep together a world of work that is likely to remain in its own loneliness and anger. We expect a great adherence to strike, factories, offices, public and private workplaces... A great event. It's time to say enough. There's a first and there's one after Suviana's accident." &nbsp;
