&nbsp;
"We're talking about a continuous massacre, a civil war. Every year there are 1040 deaths and 500 thousand accidents, a theme on which, as trade union organizations, we are asking the government for precise measures which have not yet been taken. For this reason, tomorrow we will make four hours of strike, to draw everyone to the attention to this issue. In Emilia-Romagna there will be eight hours of strike, because the incident of Suviana could be avoided", said the secretary general of Uil, Pierpaolo Bombardieri, at Rtl 102.5, "a year ago, our union organization denounced the fact that it did not intervene on safety, there are documents presented on which it was said that security was not at the maximum. After a year unfortunately the tragedy has arrived".
&nbsp;
"Many of these accidents can be avoided. And they are not accidents, when there are no interventions about murders," Bombardieri continued, "our union organization had written saying that there were procedures and systems to improve. Unfortunately, there were no answers. In a logic in which <a href="https://www.agi.it/economic/news/2024-02-26/morti-occupa-building-sesto-fiorentino-25458532/"> contracts at the lowest and cascade sub-contracts</a> take account only of profit, profit, and do not respect human life, then we have tragedies. I repeat, in many cases this is not an accident, they are real murders. Because when to earn an hour, or a thousand euros, or a contract, it does not intervene on safety and you lose a human life". &nbsp;
<h2> The conditions of the injured
The conditions of one of the five technicians who were seriously injured in the explosion are particularly serious. The man - admitted, in reserved prognosis, in the Reanimation department of the burn center of Pisa - has serious burns in different parts of the body and would be in danger of life.
&nbsp;
One of the two wounded who had been admitted in the department large burnt-outs of the hospital Bufalini of Cesena, a twenty-five years old, was discharged with a 30-day prognosis, learned from the management of the structure. The other, the most serious, of 42 years, is sedated and in intensive therapy with burns on almost 20% of the body and problems to the respiratory apparatus from inhalation of heat.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
In reanimation at the hospital of Parma there is another injured worker, 54 years old, in stationary but critical conditions for serious burns on 40%-50% of the body. In prognosis, the thirty-five-year-old admitted to the hospital Sant'Orsola in Bologna.
